<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06151e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06151e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06151e"> 151(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> slanderer / old serpent / Adversary / Prince of Power of air / &mdash; this world / roaring lion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;THE DEVIL AND ALL HIS WORKS.&rdquo;&mdash;The <mark>Slanderer</mark>. Satan means literary the <mark>Adversary</mark>; he is also called the Tempter, the Evil One; the <mark>Prince of this world</mark>, the <mark>Prince of the power of the air</mark>, the <mark>old Serpent</mark>, a <mark>roaring lion</mark>. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 10-11</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
